import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { Modal } from './Modal';

interface AboutModalProps {
  onClose: () => void;
}

/**
 * About Modal Component
 * Shows the origin story of Neuman Brain with 2 narrative versions:
 * 1. Executive/Epic version
 * 2. Realistic/Captivating version
 */
export const AboutModal: React.FC<AboutModalProps> = ({ onClose }) => {
  const [selectedNarrative, setSelectedNarrative] = useState<'executive' | 'realistic'>('realistic');

  const executiveNarrative = `As a principal engineer across multiple industries—aerospace, software, automotive, and defense—I've orchestrated transformative solutions that defined entire sectors. From architecting mission-critical systems managing billions in revenue to pioneering next-generation frameworks adopted by Fortune 500 companies, my career has been a testament to engineering excellence at epic proportions.

But despite access to every premium productivity tool in existence—Notion, Obsidian, Linear, ClickUp, Asana—I encountered a fundamental paradox: these tools either compromised privacy by hoarding user data in their clouds, or sacrificed essential features in the name of local-first architecture. The industry presented a false choice: powerful features OR privacy. Never both.

This unacceptable trade-off sparked the genesis of Neuman Brain—a revolutionary personal knowledge management system engineered to dominate both dimensions simultaneously.

**The Vision**: A zero-compromise productivity powerhouse that rivals enterprise-grade tools while guaranteeing absolute data sovereignty. Every byte stays on your device. No cloud lock-in. No surveillance capitalism. No data mining. Just pure, unfiltered productivity at your command.

**The Architecture**: Built on cutting-edge web technologies—React 19, TypeScript 5.9, IndexedDB for 50GB+ local storage—with military-grade encryption (AES-256-CBC) and a modular widget system that scales infinitely. This isn't just another productivity app; it's a new paradigm.

**The Mission**: Democratize enterprise-level productivity tools while championing digital privacy rights. Every feature, every line of code, every architectural decision serves a singular purpose: empowering individuals to reclaim control of their digital workspace without sacrificing power.

Neuman Brain represents the culmination of decades of engineering leadership—a first-principles reimagining of what personal productivity software should be in an era where privacy is a luxury most tools refuse to provide.`;

  const realisticNarrative = `I'm a software engineer who's spent years bouncing between productivity tools, always frustrated by the same problem: the best tools require trusting them with all my data.

I loved Notion's flexibility but hated their cloud dependency. Obsidian's local - first approach was refreshing, but it lacked the polish and features I needed for project management.Linear and ClickUp were powerful but locked everything behind their servers.Every tool forced me to choose: rich features with privacy concerns, or privacy with feature compromises.

As someone who values both productivity and privacy, this felt fundamentally broken.

So I started building Neuman Brain—not as a massive enterprise project, but as a solution to my own needs.I wanted notes, tasks, calendar, and time tracking that worked seamlessly together, stored locally on my device, with no cloud dependency unless I explicitly chose it.

The journey has been both challenging and rewarding.Building from first principles meant rethinking common assumptions: Why can't IndexedDB handle 50GB+ of data? Why can't client - side encryption be fast and secure ? Why can't a local-first app feel as polished as cloud-based competitors?

  ** The Core Philosophy **: Privacy and power aren't mutually exclusive. You shouldn't have to sacrifice one for the other.

** The Technology **: Modern web platform capabilities—IndexedDB, WebCrypto API, File System Access API—finally make it possible to build truly powerful local - first applications.Neuman Brain leverages these technologies to deliver enterprise - grade features without enterprise - grade surveillance.

** The Vision **: Create a productivity tool that respects your privacy as much as it enhances your productivity.Every feature is designed local - first, with cloud sync as an optional, encrypted add - on(coming Q2 2026).

This is an ongoing project—around 1 % complete with 99 % of the vision still ahead.But that's exactly the point: build the perfect foundation now, and everything else becomes possible. I'm documenting the journey, sharing the code, and building in public because I believe this approach represents the future of personal productivity software.

If you value your privacy and your productivity equally, I hope Neuman Brain becomes as useful to you as it has been to me.`;

